What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    double a { 0.1 };
    double b { 0.2 };
    double c { 0.3 };
    std::cout << (a + b == c) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

What does this program print? (Assume a 64-bit system where `long double` is 16 bytes.)

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    std::cout << sizeof(float)  << "\n";
    std::cout << sizeof(double) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

A programmer wants to check if two computed values are equal, but the comparison never works as expected. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    double result { 1.0 / 3.0 * 3.0 };
    double expected { 1.0 };
    std::cout << (result == expected) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
